The paper discusses path- and trajectory planning for autonomous vehicles, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of model predictive control (MPC) and machine learning techniques for trajectory generation suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions perception systems, which could involve computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. Finally, the paper discusses the need for generalized approaches, which could involve machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
